# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Added
- **Layer 1**: DO Spaces remote state backend (`backend.tf.jinja` +
  `init.sh.jinja` to forward credentials to `tofu init -backend-config`).
- **Layer 2**: Bootstrap-secret rotation embedded in cloud-init
  (`rotate-bootstrap-secret.sh`) — mints a fresh Infisical Machine Identity
  client secret on first boot via the Universal Auth API, atomically swaps
  `.infisical-auth.env`, revokes the v1 secret left behind in `terraform.tfvars`.
- **Path C**: Thin cloud-init + ansible app layer. Cloud-init only does
  first-boot host bootstrap (Docker, Infisical CLI, auth file, rotation).
  `ansible/deploy.yml.jinja` owns compose, Caddyfile, backup cron, and the
  `docker compose up` lifecycle.
- **Auto-tagging**: `ansible/deploy.yml.jinja` invokes `scripts/tag-droplet.sh`
  to maintain `commit-<sha>` and feature tags (`skinny-backup`, etc.) on the
  droplet for fleet discovery.
- **SSH allowlist**: New `ssh_source_cidrs` copier var pins the firewall
  ingress to specific CIDRs. Default is wide-open; production should pin
  to admin /32 or VPN.
- **Caddy log file**: Bind-mounts `/var/log/caddy` from host so otel-agent
  (filelog/caddy receiver) can read structured access logs.
- AIO Sandbox deployment template (initial release)
- Docker Compose setup with Caddy reverse proxy and sandbox container
- OpenTofu infrastructure configuration for DigitalOcean droplets
- Infisical secrets management integration
- Backup and restore scripts for workspace volumes
- Local development support
- VNC browser access, VSCode Server, Jupyter Notebook
- MCP server hub for agent integration

### Changed
- Pinned default `sandbox_image` to `ghcr.io/agent-infra/sandbox:0.4.0`
  (was `:latest` — a reproducibility footgun).
- Infisical CLI install switched from legacy `install-cli.sh` (capped at
  v0.38) to the `artifacts-cli.infisical.com` apt repo.
- Use `community.docker.docker_image_pull` (CLI-based) instead of
  `community.docker.docker_image` (requires python3-docker SDK that slim
  cloud-init doesn't install).
- Pinned `community.docker:==3.13.0` in ansible-galaxy install.

### Security
- Secrets managed via Infisical (not in git)
- Bootstrap secret rotated on first boot (Layer 2) — v1 in tfstate/DO
  metadata is dead within minutes of `tofu apply`.
- Automatic TLS via Caddy/Let's Encrypt
- Firewall with SSH source CIDR pinning (`ssh_source_cidrs`)
- JWT-based API authentication
- Caddy container hardened (`cap_drop: [ALL]` + `cap_add: NET_BIND_SERVICE`,
  `no-new-privileges:true`). The sandbox container intentionally does NOT
  have this hardening because the in-container browser/VNC stack needs
  `seccomp=unconfined` and broader process privileges — this is the same
  posture as upstream `agent-infra/sandbox`. Trade-off is acceptable: the
  sandbox runs untrusted agent workloads in its own container/network
  boundary, with no host-mount escape paths beyond the `_workspace` volume.
